data.enText: a unit of information stored in a computer, equal to 8 bits . A computer's memory is measured in bytes .

tr: a sequence of 8 bits (enough to represent one character of alphanumeric data) processed as a single unit of information

value.def: In computing, a byte is a unit of storage approximately equivalent to one printed character.
value.tran: 字节（计算机存储单位，约等于一个印刷字符）
